  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best small classes for freshmen at Hawaii Pacific University?",
  "response": "Hawaii Pacific University (HPU) offers a variety of small classes that are ideal for freshmen, providing a more personalized learning experience. While the \"best\" classes can vary depending on your interests and academic goals, here are some popular and highly recommended options for freshmen:\n\n### 1. **First-Year Seminar (FYS)**\n   - **Course Example:** FYS 1000 - First-Year Seminar\n   - **Why It's Great:** Designed specifically for freshmen, these small seminars focus on critical thinking, writing, and academic success. Topics vary by instructor, but all aim to ease the transition to college life.\n\n### 2. **Introduction to Psychology (PSY 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** This course provides an overview of psychological principles and is often taught in small sections. It\u2019s a great way to explore the field of psychology or fulfill a social science requirement.\n\n### 3. **Introduction to Sociology (SOC 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** This course examines social behavior and institutions, offering insights into how society functions. Small class sizes allow for engaging discussions and critical analysis.\n\n### 4. **English Composition (ENG 1100)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Essential for all students, this course focuses on developing strong writing skills. Freshman sections are often small, allowing for individualized feedback from instructors.\n\n### 5. **Introduction to Environmental Science (ENV 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** This course explores environmental issues and is particularly relevant given HPU\u2019s location in Hawaii. Small classes often include hands-on activities and field trips.\n\n### 6. **Introduction to Hawaiian Studies (HAW 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Learn about Hawaiian culture, history, and language in a small, interactive setting. This course is especially meaningful for students studying in Hawaii.\n\n### 7. **Public Speaking (COM 2100)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** This course helps build confidence and communication skills. Small class sizes provide a supportive environment for practicing and improving public speaking.\n\n### 8. **Introduction to Marine Biology (BIO 1200)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Given HPU\u2019s proximity to the ocean, this course often includes field trips and lab work, making it both educational and fun. Small classes ensure personalized attention.\n\n### 9. **Introduction to Business (BUS 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** This course provides a broad overview of business principles and is a good starting point for students considering a business major. Small classes facilitate active participation and discussion.\n\n### 10. **Introduction to Health and Wellness (HLTH 1000)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Focuses on personal health and wellness, offering practical knowledge that is beneficial for all students. Small class sizes encourage interaction and personal attention.\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Best Small Class:\n- **Check Class Size:** Look for classes with a low student-to-teacher ratio.\n- **Read Reviews:** Use Rate My Professors or similar sites to get feedback on instructors.\n- **Consult an Advisor:** Academic advisors can provide personalized recommendations based on your major and interests.\n- **Consider Your Schedule:** Make sure the class fits well within your academic plan and doesn\u2019t overload you.\n\nBy selecting classes that align with your interests and provide a supportive learning environment, you can make the most of your freshman year at HPU.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
